E-mails that we forget to send, voice messages that we never receive, innocent lies that annoy us almost more: these are things that “beautify” a workplace’s daily life.
The question is whether we are getting used to these problems or whether we are addressing the challenge and consciously avoiding ambiguous situations, causing trouble to others.
Examples.
