That you missed an appointment?
At best he’s sorry and tries to fix things by calling the marketing service to tell them he forgot to pass the message (this is the least common solution).
In most cases, this is done with excuses.
Before you have painful explanations, it is helpful to think about how you can cause unpleasant moments to your colleagues and make efforts to avoid them.
Are you borrowing something that doesn't belong to you?
There’s nothing more annoying than wanting to take a file, an office tool, or the phone and you can’t find them anywhere.
Do you remember the day before you put the stapler on the desk but she disappeared the next morning?
