Congress approves transposition of the Mifid, which came into force on November 1.
In addition to its parliamentary formality, which ended today with the vote of the Congress on the amendments incorporated into the bill in the Senate, the Government submitted to a public hearing the regulation that will develop the new law, with the aim of its entry into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the efforts made by MPs and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulation to ensure investor protection and to regulate in detail the activities of organizations for the effective functioning of markets.
The Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Act, involves the modernization of financial markets, as it strengthens investor protection, improves the powers of the leaders of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promotes cooperation between the various leaders of the European Union.
The new regulation will provide financial consulting services for specialized social reasons as well as for natural or legal persons and create a new type of financial services (ESIS), financial consulting companies (FIs), which merge with securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it increases the number of systems for the execution of transactions on financial instruments, so that it is possible to add multilateral trading systems and order internationalization systems to the regulated secondary markets, which face competition from current exchange managers.
The Act also obliges investment services companies to disclose information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management on the market, and obliges them to keep a record of all operations they carry out, to facilitate control on the part of the CNMV.
A number of changes have been added through the Congressional Economic Commission, one of which highlights that securitized debt will be considered a "complex" financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, which has proven itself with what happened with the debt of high-risk U.S. mortgages.
In addition, they took advantage of the transition of management has taken advantage of to legally delineate the functions that graduates in Economics may have 30 years after 1977, the royal decree that delineates the professional functions reserved for economists was approved.
For its part, the Senate has incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as that of the mediator, who will work on behalf of a company, who will not require the authorization of the CNMV and who will be able to lend its product marketing services and attract new customers to different investment firms at the same time.
