What insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible harms, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, driving licence age, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use that is actually made, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
And that is, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is realized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium awarded and in exchange it becomes responsible for the obligation to pay the compensation in case of a claim.
The premium is the price of insurance, which is established by taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, driving licence age, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured, or actual use, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on the statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the rate to be paid.
That’s why people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that these people have a lower rate of harm than their caution.
Similarly, by using censuses, the companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the probability of having an accident.
By increasing the frequency, the probabilities increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the price of the premium.
It is for this reason that the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
We will present here the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers it a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 must face various drawbacks when entering into a contract with an insurance at an affordable price, such as poor driving experience and old-age driving license.
While the ideal to be well insured is risk-free insurance, there are other more economical options.
The most predictable drivers can opt for any risk insurance with franchise, so that they get insurance coverage at any risk but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
“The part of the amount of the claim that the customer pays will be determined based on the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount will be,” said Luis Noguera, the Spanish head of First Europe, an online insurance broker.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but for those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under the age of 25 try to be careful and avoid claims as far as possible, as this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the base rate owned by the company.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic rate.
"The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its profits.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses,” Noguera explained.
Over the age of 25 it becomes easier for drivers to contract with insurance, as the rate of claims is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is better to choose any risk insurance with franchise.
“Normally, young people cannot benefit from the experience previously gained after an accident,” says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the ‘fear of the novice’ has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children it is better that he negotiates insurance at any risk, as long as his economic situation allows him.
Child marriages are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest rate of claims, because the increases will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be any risk insurance with franchise (can be 300 euros), or extended third-party insurance from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of credit.
“They have a more relaxed drive and they have a greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchisees,” says Luis Noguera.
For retirees an insurance at any risk with franchise is preferable (being this one of 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of credit.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible harms, but also because it represents an important expense, that is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that suits us most depending on our personal situation.
