Loyal troops in power shielded the area around the respectable hotel.
The President convened an urgent meeting of the Security Cabinet.
The National Security Adviser Norberto Gonzales condemned the actions of the soldiers.
“People have enough,” Trillanes said.
“We call on people to join us.”
General Danilo Lim, who commanded before the Scouts Rangers elite unit, said other units in the army soon wanted to join the march.
